# MANDATORY: Lint Before Push

**Never push without passing local format and lint checks first.**

Before any `git push`, run these commands from the repository root and fix all failures:

```bash
scripts/check-format.sh
cmake --preset lint
cmake --build --preset lint --parallel
```

If you changed C++ sources, also run:

```bash
cmake --preset debug
cmake --build --preset debug --parallel
ctest --preset debug
```

## Rules

1. Run `scripts/check-format.sh` on every commit that touches `src/` or `tests/`.
2. If format check fails, run `clang-format -i` on the reported files, then re-check.
3. Do not push when CI lint/format would fail.
4. Treat a failed local format check as a blocker — same severity as a failing test.

## Quick format fix

```bash
git ls-files 'src/*.cpp' 'src/*.hpp' 'tests/*.cpp' 'tests/*.hpp' \
  | xargs clang-format -i
scripts/check-format.sh
```
